The paper deals with topics related to computational complexity (bias of multilinear forms), information theory (correlation between multilinear forms and lower degree polynomials), data structures (tensor rank), discrete mathematics (polynomials, tensors), and computational geometry (tensor rank lower bounds for finite field multiplication). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
